metadata.name: Champlain Gold
metadata.description:
Lake Champlain separates Vermont and New York while it flows North to its outlet at the Richelieu River in Quebec in Canada. This picture showcases Burton Island and Ball Island with Grand Isle and the Appalachian Mountains, in NY, in the background.
